  forall_imp fun _x ‚Ü¶ .imp fun _l ‚Ü¶ .imp_right <| @hEF _
```

This lemma shows that if `E ‚äÜ F` and `E` is relatively dense with respect to `l`, then `F` is also relatively dense with respect to `l`.

```tactics
